==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indecent
<hw>In*de"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indecens</ets> unseemly, unbecoming: cf. F.
<ets>ind⟦eacute⟧cent</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Decent</er>.]</ety> <def>Not decent; unfit to be seen or heard;
offensive to modesty and delicacy; <as>as, <ex>indecent</ex>
language</as>.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Unbecoming; indecorous; indelicate; unseemly;
immodest; gross; shameful; impure; improper; obscene; filthy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indecently</ent>⟦br⟧
